  "prompt": "Will I be arrested reentering the US with a bench warrant?",
  "response": "If you have a bench warrant out for your arrest and you attempt to reenter the United States, it is possible that you could be arrested at the border or airport. A bench warrant typically indicates that a judge has issued a warrant for your arrest due to failure to appear in court or comply with a court order. Law enforcement agencies, including those at border control, can access warrant databases, which means they may be aware of the warrant when you attempt to enter the country.\n\nIt is advisable to address the bench warrant before attempting to reenter the U.S. Consulting with a legal professional who can provide advice based on your specific situation is also a good idea.",
